This paper focuses on pedestrian trajectory prediction, which is a common problem in computer vision (CV) and robotics (RO) applications. The proposed method uses a generative model and social attention network, which are both common techniques in machine learning (ML) and artificial intelligence (AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of latent variable distributions, which is a common topic in statistics and information theory (SI). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV, cs.LG, and cs.RO, followed by cs.AI and cs.SI.
